content.description: A steep juggy start leads up first 4 bolts. Crux is soon after going left on small holds. Continue up 2 more bolts to another traversing crux. Fight the pump on good holds until close to the corner. Things ease up for the rest of the route. Follow bolts up dihedral to fixed chains.
content.location: Bottom right route on the TrenchTown Wall.

climbs.name: Natural Mystic
climbs.fa: Bolted, Preped, and FA by Michele Pratt

content.description: An awkard start to a great wall of that red tuff everyone loves at Smith. Classic smith climbing on a crimpy face with a little arete climbing mixed in. The crux is getting established on the face and getting onto the slab.
content.protection: 12 bolts. anchors are fixed with steel carabiners
content.location: Most left route on the trench town wall

climbs.name: The Movement
climbs.fa: FA, Bolted, and prepped by Alan Collins

content.description: Still in need of a little traffic at the start. Start out on steep 5.11+ climbing for the first 3 or 4 bolts. Work your way up to a baffling arete crux and link into the same end of the habit.
content.location: Just to the right of The Habit. Share the end.

climbs.name: The Habit
climbs.fa: Bolted, Preped, and FA by Alex Reed

content.description: Alex Reed's first legit route he put up. Besides a 5.7 route called "Munchies", this was Alex's first proud developed route. Boulder your way up a bulge to get established in an eye catching dihedral. Funk your way through the dihedral only to find yourself at the real heartbreaker crux going for the chains. A tough one to send.
content.protection: 12 bolts and fixed anchors with steel carabiners
content.location: Start in the center of the wall on the 2nd most left route

content.description: Morning sun and evening shade. It tends to always be windy here for some reason. Climb up varied terrain on classic red welded tuff patina! The left side of the wall tends to be more vertical and the right side gets steeper with larger features to climb.
